      "content": "While it's true that many people adjust their warfarin dosage when they feel stable, it's not a straightforward decision to make on your own. The risk of a sudden stroke or other complications from a sudden change in warfarin dosage isn't just low; it's potentially life-threatening. Warfarin's effects are highly individualized, and even a slight deviation from your prescribed dose can lead to dangerous outcomes. I strongly advise against making any changes to your medication without consulting your healthcare provider. They can provide a safe and monitored approach to any necessary adjustments. Your health and safety are paramount.",
